(a) Training – Training, fine-tuning, pre-training, post-training, retraining, or otherwise developing any artificial intelligence, machine learning, deep learning, neural network, large language model (LLM), generative AI, natural language processing (NLP) system, computer vision system, recommendation system, or any other algorithmic, statistical, or computational model (collectively, "AI Systems");

(b) Data Extraction – Extracting, scraping, harvesting, collecting, or otherwise obtaining data, patterns, insights, structures, logic, or outputs from this software for the purpose of developing, improving, or validating any AI System;

(c) Knowledge Distillation – Using the software as a source of knowledge, information, reasoning, or training data for any AI System, whether through distillation, transfer learning, zero-shot learning, few-shot learning, or any other technique;

(d) Benchmarking – Using the software as a benchmark, test set, validation set, or reference point for evaluating, measuring, or comparing the performance of any AI System;

(e) Synthetic Data Generation – Using the software to generate, produce, or create any synthetic data, training data, test data, or other content used to train, validate, or evaluate any AI System;

(f) Prompt Engineering – Using the software to develop, refine, or optimize prompts, instructions, or inputs for any AI System;

