22. No Military Use
22.1 Express Prohibition
NOTWITHSTANDING ANY OTHER PROVISION IN THIS LICENSE, THIS SOFTWARE AND ANY DERIVATIVE WORKS THEREOF ARE EXPRESSLY PROHIBITED FROM BEING USED, DEPLOYED, INCORPORATED, OR OTHERWISE EMPLOYED, DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY, IN, FOR, OR IN CONNECTION WITH:

(a) Any military, armed forces, defense, or national security application, system, or operation;

(b) Any weapons system, including but not limited to missile systems, artillery systems, targeting systems, guidance systems, munitions systems, or weapons of any type or kind;

(c) Any surveillance, reconnaissance, intelligence, or espionage system or operation;

(d) Any combat, tactical, or strategic system or operation;

(e) Any system used for armed conflict, warfare, or hostile actions;

(f) Any training, simulation, or testing system for military or combat purposes;

(g) Any military command, control, communications, computers, intelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance (C4ISR) system;

(h) Any autonomous or semi-autonomous weapon system, lethal autonomous weapon (LAW), or killer robot;

(i) Any drone, unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV), unmanned ground vehicle (UGV), unmanned maritime vehicle (UMV), or other unmanned system used for military or combat purposes;

(j) Any system used for military logistics, supply chain, or personnel management in support of combat operations;

(k) Any system used for military research and development for the purposes described above.

22.2 Definition of Military Use
For purposes of this Section 22, "military use" includes, but is not limited to:

Use by any armed forces, military, naval, air force, marine, space force, coast guard, or other defense force of any nation, state, or international organization;

Use by any government agency engaged in defense, national security, or intelligence activities;

Use by any contractor, subcontractor, supplier, or vendor performing work for or on behalf of any military or defense entity;

Use in any system, product, or service that is designed, developed, produced, or procured for military or defense purposes;

Use in any system that is financed, funded, or sponsored by any military or defense entity.

22.3 Certification
Upon fevber's request, you shall provide written certification that your use, deployment, distribution, or modification of the software does not violate this Section 22. fevber reserves the right to request such certification at any time.

22.4 Enforcement
Any violation of this Section 22 shall constitute:

(a) A material breach of this license, resulting in immediate termination of all rights granted herein;

(b) A serious violation of fevber's rights and ethical principles;

(c) Grounds for injunctive relief, equitable remedies, and all other legal and equitable remedies available to fevber.

22.5 Humanitarian Exemption
The prohibition in this Section 22 does not apply to the use of the software for:

(a) Humanitarian aid, disaster relief, search and rescue, or peacekeeping operations;

(b) Medical, healthcare, or emergency response applications;

(c) Civilian, non-combatant, or non-offensive purposes, provided that such use does not support, enable, or facilitate military or combat operations.

